{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Saffron and sage bread","content":["Place dried fruit into mixing bowl and chop <b>4 sec\/speed 6<b>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside.","Place nuts into mixing bowl and chop <b>2 sec\/speed 5<b>. Transfer into bowl with dried fruit and set aside.","Place water, saffron, bay leaf and allspice berries into mixing bowl and cook <b>6 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Transfer into a small bowl and allow to cool to room temperature. Strain, using a fine-mesh sieve, into a jug then discard solids and set infused water aside. Rinse and dry mixing bowl.","Place flour and yeast into mixing bowl and mix <b>10 sec\/speed 4<b>.","Add honey, 2 of the eggs, butter, milk and salt and knead <b>2 min\/<b>, slowly adding infused water through hole in mixing bowl lid until combined.","Add sage, cinnamon and reserved dried fruits and nuts and knead <b>1 min\/<b>. Transfer onto a silicone bread mat or lightly floured work surface and shape into a ball. Wrap dough in bread mat or place into an oiled bowl and cover with plastic wrap. Leave to prove until doubled in size (approx. 2 hours). Clean and dry mixing bowl.","Preheat oven to 170°C. Line a large baking tray (30 x 40 cm) with baking paper and set aside.","Transfer dough onto a lightly floured work surface and divide into 12 equal portions (see Tips). Form into small balls and arrange on prepared baking tray in a Christmas tree shape. Whisk remaining egg in a small bowl and brush each ball with egg. Bake for 30-35 minutes (170°C), rotating tray if necessary after 20 minutes to ensure even baking, until golden brown and sounds hollow when tapped."]},{"title":"Ginger butter","content":["Place glacé ginger into mixing bowl and chop <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add ground ginger and butter and blend <b>10 sec\/speed 4<b>. Transfer into a sealable container and set aside in refrigerator until ready to serve.","Serve bread with butter."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Saffron and sage bread","content":["200 g mixed dried fruit (e.g. apricots, cranberries, sultanas)","100 g nuts (e.g. walnuts, pecans, pistachios)","150 g water","1 pinch saffron","1 dried bay leaf","4 allspice berries","500 g baker's flour","10 g dried instant yeast","50 g honey","3 eggs","40 g unsalted butter, softened","150 g full cream milk","1 pinch salt","15 fresh sage leaves, finely chopped","1 tsp ground cinnamon"]},{"title":"Ginger butter","content":["120 g glacé ginger","1 tsp ground ginger","150 g unsalted butter, cut into cubes (2 cm)"]}],"id":"r119780","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-KbcEEexqs5I\/XZWqSDDkF7I\/AAAAAAAAfVo\/CJMrhOFjBhEIiDckOgyokuX-JKGBphOUQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_HsEBn4OKMK0tKIFT.png","title":"Celebration saffron and sage bread with ginger butter","publishedAt":"2017-01-22T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"9.6 g","fat":"20.4 g","uom":"per 1 portions","carbohydrates":"55.5 g","calories":"1878 kJ \/ 447 kcal"},"usefulItems":"bowl, fine mesh sieve, jug, small bowl , plastic wrap, silicone bread mat, baking tray (30 x 40 cm), baking paper, whisk, pastry brush, sealable container, oven, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["You can replace allspice berries with whole cloves in this recipe.","Instead of forming into balls, dough can be plaited and arranged in a wreath shape."],"basicInfo":["easy","25m","3h","12 portions"]}